title: 820-2914 no power
message:
"AL_SYS_PWRGD at 0.048V"
Fix that problem.

First, remove Q7950.
If still low, start removing (one by one) the power goods resistors; keep in place R7967.

title: 820-2914 no power
message: Removed Q7950 and the power good resistors leaving R7967 in place but still low

title: 820-2914 no power
message: Do you have 3V at pin 1/R7967?

title: 820-2914 no power
message: Yes

title: 820-2914 no power
message:
Then R7967 is bad.
If is good and has 3V on pin 1, same voltage must appear on pin 2, if there is no other component connected.
Or you forgot some power good resistor...

title: 820-2914 no power
message: Solved. Removing power good resistors lead to a bad U7100
